claim.claim-text:
A method of wireless communication by a user equipment, UE, (104, 350, 1002) comprising:
identifying (902) a first subband in a plurality of subbands of an orthogonal frequency division multiplexed, OFDM, symbol for a first reference signal, RS, transmitted by a base station (102, 310, 1050), wherein the first RS comprises a first common RS, CRS;
determining (904) a first RS placement for the first RS in the first subband comprised in the plurality of subbands of the OFDM symbol, wherein the first RS placement is dependent upon a cell identifier, cell ID, of the base station and said determining comprises determining a cell ID dependent frequency shift;
receiving (906) the first RS from the base station based on the determined first RS placement;
identifying (907) a second subband in the plurality of subbands of the OFDM symbol for a second RS;
determining (909) a second RS placement for a second RS in the second subband comprised in the plurality of subbands of the OFDM symbol and different from the first subband, wherein the second RS placement is independent of the cell ID of the base station, and wherein the second RS comprises a UE specific RS and the second RS placement is determined without the cell ID frequency shift; and
receiving (912) the second RS from the base station based on the determined second RS placement.
